#: ../../S/Slowlaris.rst:9
msgid ""
"[Usenet; poss. from the variety of prosimian called a \"slow loris\". The "
"variant ‘Slowlartus’ is also common, related to :ref:`LART`\\] Common "
"hackish term for Solaris, Sun's System VR4 version of Unix that came out of "
"the standardization wars of the early 1990s. So named because especially on "
"older hardware, responsiveness was much less crisp than under the preceding "
"SunOS. Early releases of Solaris (that is, Solaris 2, as some "
":ref:`marketroid`\\s at Sun retroactively rechristened SunOS as Solaris 1) "
"were quite buggy, and Sun was forced by customer demand to support SunOS for"
" quite some time. Newer versions are acknowledged to be among the best "
"commercial Unix variants in 1998, but still lose single-processor benchmarks"
" to Sparc :ref:`Linux`\\. Compare :ref:`HP-SUX`\\, :ref:`sun-stools`\\."
msgstr ""
"[Usenet; おそらく「slow loris(スローロリス)」と呼ばれる原猿の一種から。変種‘Slowlartus’も一般的で、\\ "
":ref:`LART`\\ に関連する] 1990年代初頭の標準化戦争から生まれた、SunのSystem "
"VR4版UnixであるSolarisを指す、ハッカーらしい一般的な用語。とくに古いハードウェアでは、先行するSunOSと比べて反応がはるかにきびきびしていなかったことからこう名付けられた。Solarisの初期リリース(つまりSolaris"
" 2。Sunの一部の\\ :ref:`marketroid`\\ はSunOSをさかのぼってSolaris "
"1と改名した)はかなりバグが多く、Sunは顧客の需要に押されてSunOSをかなり長い間サポートせざるを得なかった。新しいバージョンは1998年時点で最良の商用Unix系のひとつと認められているが、それでもシングルプロセッサのベンチマークではSparc版\\"
" :ref:`Linux`\\ に敗れる。\\ :ref:`HP-SUX`\\ 、\\ :ref:`sun-stools`\\ と比較せよ。"
